.SH NAME
inkjet \- Create interactive CLIs and execute Markdown
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]inkjet\f[R]
[\-\-interactive][\-\-preview][\-\-help][\-\-version][\-\-inkfile=inkjet.md]
\f[I]subcommand\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
With \f[CR]inkjet\f[R] you can build interactive CLIs from your existing
Markdown.
These CLIs can be as simple as a list of common tasks such as
\f[CR]test\f[R], \f[CR]build\f[R], and \f[CR]lint\f[R] or as complex
applications with subcommands, flags, and options.
All of this defined in a simple Markdown file that is both a
\f[B]human\-readable document\f[R] and a \f[B]command definition\f[R]!
Your code is documentation and your documentation is code.
Because Markdown is documentation focused, the format encourages
descriptive text.
This allows others to easily get started with your project\(cqs
development setup by simply reading your \f[CR]inkjet.md\f[R].
.SH USE CASES
.SS Rapid CLI development
Inkjet is the fastest path to building and distributing custom command
line apps.
Because you ship a single Markdown file, you can distribute it with any
web server.
You can quickly convert your bash aliases to a CLI interface or use
multiple languages to build an advanced app.
It is all wrapped up with your documentation in a single readable file.
.SS Project specific tasks
You have a project with a bunch of random build and development scripts
or an unwieldy \f[CR]Makefile\f[R].
Simplify by having a single, readable file for your team members to add
and modify existing tasks.
.SS Global system utility
You want a global utility CLI for various system tasks such as backing
up directories or renaming multiple files.
This is easily possible by making a bash alias for
\f[CR]inkjet \-\-inkfile \(ti/my\-global\-inkjet.md\f[R].
.SS Executable interactive tutorials and guides
Blog posts and tutorials often contain text with blocks of code walking
the reader through the process of creating or installing an application
or using a project.
Markdown is commonly used as the authoring format for these guides.
Using Inkjet\(cqs interactive capabilities, it is simple to take an
existing tutorial and distribute an executable documentation file.
Users can download your tutorial and read it, preview code blocks, and
execute each step inside their terminals.
